## Data Models

### Subject
```typescript
interface Subject {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  progress: number;
  concepts: Concept[];
  prerequisites: string[];
  videosCount: number;
  completedVideos: number;
  knowledgeGraph: GraphData;
}
```

### UserProgress
```typescript
interface UserProgress {
  userId: string;
  subjects: {
    [subjectId: string]: {
      progress: number;
      lastActivity: Date;
      completedVideos: string[];
      masteredConcepts: string[];
      quizScores: {
        [quizId: string]: number;
      };
      reflections: Reflection[];
    }
  };
  learningStreak: number;
  totalStudyTime: number;
  weeklyGoals: {
    target: number;
    achieved: number;
  };
}
```

## Firebase Implementation

### Collections
1. subjects
   - Subject metadata
   - Knowledge graph data
   - Core concepts

2. userProgress
   - Learning progress
   - Activity history
   - Achievement data

3. conceptMastery
   - User-specific concept mastery
   - Learning pathways
   - Prerequisites tracking

### Cloud Functions
1. updateUserProgress
   - Tracks video completion
   - Updates mastery levels
   - Maintains learning streaks

2. generateInsights
   - Analyzes learning patterns
   - Suggests next steps
   - Identifies knowledge gaps

3. updateKnowledgeGraph
   - Maintains concept relationships
   - Updates prerequisite chains
   - Tracks mastery dependencies

## Success Metrics
- User engagement (time spent learning)
- Completion rates
- Knowledge retention (quiz scores)
- User satisfaction
- Learning streak maintenance

## INTJ-Specific Features
- Systematic organization of knowledge
- Clear progress metrics
- Deep subject exploration
- Cross-topic connections
- Clean, focused interface
- Structured learning paths
- Analytical insights
